output.crosstab_text:
Among those who graduated five years previously from level 7 (research) courses in all subjects and who were working during the 2021-22 tax year, the industry with the highest proportion of graduates was the same for both female and male graduates (Education). The median earnings for females in this industry were £32,700 and for males were £34,700. The biggest difference in proportions was in Human health and social work activities, where the proportion of female graduates was 10.2 % points higher than the proportion of male graduates.

The biggest difference in median earnings was in Financial and insurance activities, where the median earnings of male graduates were £41,600 higher than the median earnings of female graduates. The group with the highest earnings was Male graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £95,600).
